pesticide.PPE: Long-sleeved shirt and long pants; Shoes plus socks; and Chemical-resistant gloves made out of: barrier laminate, butyl rubber ≥14 mils, nitrile rubber ≥ 14 mils, or neoprene rubber.

Safety_Information.general_Info: Harmful if swallowed. Wash hands thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet.
Safety_Information.if_Swallowed: Call a poison control center or doctor immediately for treatment advice. Have person sip a glass of water if able to swallow. DO NOT induce vomiting unless told to do so by a poison control center or doctor. DO NOT give anything by mouth to an unconscious person.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: The use of Atropine is contraindicated. Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor, or going for treatment.
